{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 750 g of the tomatoes into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add remaining 750 g of tomatoes and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add bay leaf, oregano, salt and sugar and cook <b>60 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid. Cook for a further <b>30 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>30-45 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid, to desired consistency."," <strong>Insert measuring cup<\/strong>. Blend <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b><strong>-9, increasing speed gradually from speed 4 to speed 9<\/strong>.","Allow mixture to cool slightly, then transfer to a sterilised sealable jar. Top with a thin layer of oil and cool to room temperature. Store in refrigerator until ready to use (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1500 g Roma tomatoes, very ripe and cut into quarters","1 dried bay leaf","1 tbsp dried oregano","1 tsp salt","1 tsp white sugar","olive oil, to cover"]}],"id":"r270106","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-wd9R5xWxRUg\/XZWYJb65n-I\/AAAAAAAAd5Y\/-CB-ujxH8ZMbkoQyMs2sWLVHM8sVo2KAQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1sVzxfXS9J6K-SN7.png","title":"Tomato paste","publishedAt":"2018-04-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.7 g","fat":"0.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1.8 g","calories":"83.3 kJ \/ 19.8 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sterilised sealable jar, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Tomato paste can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 1 month or freeze in ice cube trays to store for up to 6 months.","Covering the paste with a layer of oil helps to prevent bacteria and mould from forming."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","2h 20m","24 portions"]}